00:53:07.040 --> 00:53:07.680
Heaven watches.

00:53:08.250 --> 00:53:10.200
The Lord is near to those who weep in private.

00:53:10.200 --> 00:53:12.420
Every cry you've whispered, He's caught it.

00:53:12.420 --> 00:53:14.046
Every groan, He's recorded it.

00:53:14.046 --> 00:53:17.000
Every lonely night, you were never truly alone.

00:53:17.000 --> 00:53:22.817
The solitary intercessor is never invisible to God.

00:53:22.817 --> 00:53:30.800
I never saw most of the fruit I prayed for, but years later, the cities I groaned over would erupt in revival.

00:53:30.800 --> 00:53:36.524
What you birthed in solitude becomes fire that spreads publicly.

00:53:36.524 --> 00:53:48.891
Your secret place may look empty, but it is the epicenter of something holy.

00:53:48.891 --> 00:53:54.000
Lord, I say yes to the hidden path.

00:53:54.000 --> 00:53:58.052
Strengthen me in the lonely room.

00:53:58.052 --> 00:54:06.120
Remind me that I am not alone, that You are near to those who weep in secret.

00:54:06.120 --> 00:54:08.520
I choose the narrow way.

00:54:08.520 --> 00:54:11.297
I choose the silent room.

00:54:11.297 --> 00:54:15.726
I choose the weight that no one sees.

00:54:15.726 --> 00:54:20.914
Birth through me what will one day touch thousands.

00:54:20.914 --> 00:54:23.200
Revival is conceived in groaning.

00:54:23.200 --> 00:54:26.347
Before there's glory, there's groaning.

00:54:30.933 --> 00:54:31.306
You want to know where revival starts?

00:54:31.306 --> 00:54:42.160
It's not in the sanctuary, not in the sermon, but in the sound of groaning from a soul laid bare before God.

00:54:42.160 --> 00:54:46.022
Revival is conceived in the womb of agony.

00:54:46.022 --> 00:54:52.240
It is forged in the cries of the desperate.

00:54:52.240 --> 00:54:54.496
I never birthed anything with convenience.

00:54:54.496 --> 00:54:56.800
It was painful, raw, holy travail.

00:55:00.860 --> 00:55:02.610
That groan—it was heaven's signal that something divine was being formed.

00:55:02.610 --> 00:55:07.725
Groaning isn't a charismatic gimmick; it's spiritual labor.

00:55:07.725 --> 00:55:15.760
I groaned until my body shook, until my voice was gone, until the heavens broke open.

00:55:29.956 --> 00:55:30.213
That was when revival was conceived.

00:55:30.213 --> 00:55:36.160
I never saw revival fall until I first groaned for it.

00:55:37.817 --> 00:55:40.469
The church doesn't need more noise; it needs labor pains.

00:55:52.587 --> 00:55:52.871
You must be willing to carry what you cry for.

00:55:52.871 --> 00:55:57.243
Don't pray for revival if you're not willing to carry revival.

00:56:04.978 --> 00:56:05.227
It will cost you.

00:56:06.222 --> 00:56:06.720
It will crush you.

00:56:07.164 --> 00:56:10.040
It will strip you of comfort and convenience.

00:56:13.188 --> 00:56:13.645
But if you groan long enough, it will come.

00:56:27.200 --> 00:56:27.474
And when it does, it will change everything.

00:56:27.474 --> 00:56:28.297
It's good.

00:56:28.297 --> 00:56:35.104
